  "prompt": "If I delete someone on Snapchat that I have a streak with, and my account is available for everyone to snap/chat me, will that erase the streak?",
  "response": "If you delete someone on Snapchat with whom you have a streak, the streak will **not automatically erase** just because you deleted them. However, the streak **will eventually end** if neither of you sends a snap to the other within 24 hours. Deleting someone simply removes them from your friends list, but your account being open for everyone to snap/chat you does not prevent the streak from ending if no snaps are exchanged.\n\nTo maintain the streak, you or the other person would need to continue sending snaps within the 24-hour window, even if you are no longer friends. However, if you delete them, it might be harder to coordinate or remember to keep the streak going, especially if they don\u2019t know you\u2019ve unfriended them or if your account is set to accept snaps from everyone. \n\nIn summary:\n- Deleting someone does not immediately erase the streak.\n- The streak will end if no snaps are exchanged within 24 hours.\n- If you want to keep the streak, you\u2019ll need to continue sending snaps, even after deleting them.",
